channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: PromptAttack: Probing Dialogue State Trackers with Adversarial Prompts
item.description: A key component of modern conversational systems is the Dialogue State Tracker (or DST), which models a user's goals and needs.

item.title: GP-UNIT: Generative Prior for Versatile Unsupervised Image-to-Image Translation
item.description: In this paper, we introduce a novel versatile framework, Generative Prior-guided UNsupervised Image-to-image Translation (GP-UNIT), that improves the quality, applicability and controllability of the existing translation models.

item.title: Designing a Better Asymmetric VQGAN for StableDiffusion
item.description: The training cost of our asymmetric VQGAN is cheap, and we only need to retrain a new asymmetric decoder while keeping the vanilla VQGAN encoder and StableDiffusion unchanged.

item.title: GCT-TTE: Graph Convolutional Transformer for Travel Time Estimation
item.description: This paper introduces a new transformer-based model for the problem of travel time estimation.

item.title: End-to-End Learning for Stochastic Optimization: A Bayesian Perspective
item.description: We develop a principled approach to end-to-end learning in stochastic optimization.

item.title: Patch-level Routing in Mixture-of-Experts is Provably Sample-efficient for Convolutional Neural Networks
item.description: In deep learning, mixture-of-experts (MoE) activates one or few experts (sub-networks) on a per-sample or per-token basis, resulting in significant computation reduction.

item.title: Proximity-Informed Calibration for Deep Neural Networks
item.description: Confidence calibration is central to providing accurate and interpretable uncertainty estimates, especially under safety-critical scenarios.

item.title: A novel deeponet model for learning moving-solution operators with applications to earthquake hypocenter localization
item.description: Seismicity induced by human activities poses a significant threat to public safety, emphasizing the need for accurate and timely earthquake hypocenter localization.

item.title: Rewarded soups: towards Pareto-optimal alignment by interpolating weights fine-tuned on diverse rewards
item.description: Foundation models are first pre-trained on vast unsupervised datasets and then fine-tuned on labeled data.

item.title: Unified Model for Crystalline Material Generation
item.description: One of the greatest challenges facing our society is the discovery of new innovative crystal materials with specific properties.

item.title: Training-Free Neural Active Learning with Initialization-Robustness Guarantees
item.description: To this end, we introduce our expected variance with Gaussian processes (EV-GP) criterion for neural active learning, which is theoretically guaranteed to select data points which lead to trained NNs with both (a) good predictive performances and (b) initialization robustness.

item.title: XSemPLR: Cross-Lingual Semantic Parsing in Multiple Natural Languages and Meaning Representations
item.description: However, existing CLSP models are separately proposed and evaluated on datasets of limited tasks and applications, impeding a comprehensive and unified evaluation of CLSP on a diverse range of NLs and MRs. To this end, we present XSemPLR, a unified benchmark for cross-lingual semantic parsing featured with 22 natural languages and 8 meaning representations by examining and selecting 9 existing datasets to cover 5 tasks and 164 domains.

item.title: Improving Diffusion-based Image Translation using Asymmetric Gradient Guidance
item.description: Diffusion models have shown significant progress in image translation tasks recently.

item.title: Stochastic Collapse: How Gradient Noise Attracts SGD Dynamics Towards Simpler Subnetworks
item.description: In this work, we reveal a strong implicit bias of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) that drives overly expressive networks to much simpler subnetworks, thereby dramatically reducing the number of independent parameters, and improving generalization.

item.title: SANGEET: A XML based Open Dataset for Research in Hindustani Sangeet
item.description: The dataset is intended to provide the ground truth information for music information research tasks, thereby supporting several data-driven analysis from a machine learning perspective.

item.title: PromptBench: Towards Evaluating the Robustness of Large Language Models on Adversarial Prompts
item.description: The increasing reliance on Large Language Models (LLMs) across academia and industry necessitates a comprehensive understanding of their robustness to prompts.

item.title: Youku-mPLUG: A 10 Million Large-scale Chinese Video-Language Dataset for Pre-training and Benchmarks
item.description: In addition, to facilitate a comprehensive evaluation of video-language models, we carefully build the largest human-annotated Chinese benchmarks covering three popular video-language tasks of cross-modal retrieval, video captioning, and video category classification.

item.title: Synthesising Recursive Functions for First-Order Model Counting: Challenges, Progress, and Conjectures
item.description: First-order model counting (FOMC) is a computational problem that asks to count the models of a sentence in finite-domain first-order logic.

item.title: IUTEAM1 at MEDIQA-Chat 2023: Is simple fine tuning effective for multilayer summarization of clinical conversations?
item.description: Clinical conversation summarization has become an important application of Natural language Processing.

item.title: UCTB: An Urban Computing Tool Box for Spatiotemporal Crowd Flow Prediction
item.description: To address these issues, we design and implement a spatiotemporal crowd flow prediction toolbox called UCTB (Urban Computing Tool Box), which integrates multiple spatiotemporal domain knowledge and state-of-the-art models simultaneously.

item.title: Self-Adjusting Weighted Expected Improvement for Bayesian Optimization
item.description: Bayesian Optimization (BO) is a class of surrogate-based, sample-efficient algorithms for optimizing black-box problems with small evaluation budgets.

item.title: CFDP: Common Frequency Domain Pruning
item.description: In this paper, we introduce a novel end-to-end pipeline for model pruning via the frequency domain.

item.title: 1st Place Solution for PVUW Challenge 2023: Video Panoptic Segmentation
item.description: In this report, we successfully validated the effectiveness of the decoupling strategy in video panoptic segmentation.

item.title: Git-Theta: A Git Extension for Collaborative Development of Machine Learning Models
item.description: Currently, most machine learning models are trained by centralized teams and are rarely updated.

item.title: TEC-Net: Vision Transformer Embrace Convolutional Neural Networks for Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: The hybrid architecture of convolution neural networks (CNN) and Transformer has been the most popular method for medical image segmentation.

item.title: CorrMatch: Label Propagation via Correlation Matching for Semi-Supervised Semantic Segmentation
item.description: In this paper, we present a simple but performant semi-supervised semantic segmentation approach, termed CorrMatch.

item.title: A Dataset for Deep Learning-based Bone Structure Analyses in Total Hip Arthroplasty
item.description: For THA, it is of clinical significance to analyze the bone structure from the CT images, especially to observe the structure of the acetabulum and femoral head, before the surgical procedure.

item.title: Revising deep learning methods in parking lot occupancy detection
item.description: Parking guidance systems have recently become a popular trend as a part of the smart cities' paradigm of development.

item.title: Policy-Based Self-Competition for Planning Problems
item.description: AlphaZero-type algorithms may stop improving on single-player tasks in case the value network guiding the tree search is unable to approximate the outcome of an episode sufficiently well.

item.title: Normalization Layers Are All That Sharpness-Aware Minimization Needs
item.description: Sharpness-aware minimization (SAM) was proposed to reduce sharpness of minima and has been shown to enhance generalization performance in various settings.

item.title: Arabic Dysarthric Speech Recognition Using Adversarial and Signal-Based Augmentation
item.description: We perform further validation on real English dysarthric speech showing a WER improvement of 124% compared to the baseline trained only on healthy English LJSpeech dataset.

item.title: The Two Word Test: A Semantic Benchmark for Large Language Models
item.description: We provide versions of the task that probe meaningfulness ratings on a 0-4 scale as well as binary judgments.

item.title: World Models for Math Story Problems
item.description: In this paper, we consolidate previous work on categorizing and representing math story problems and develop MathWorld, which is a graph-based semantic formalism specific for the domain of math story problems.

item.title: Multimodal Learning Without Labeled Multimodal Data: Guarantees and Applications
item.description: We propose two lower bounds based on the amount of shared information between modalities and the disagreement between separately trained unimodal classifiers, and derive an upper bound through connections to approximate algorithms for min-entropy couplings.

item.title: Can current NLI systems handle German word order? Investigating language model performance on a new German challenge set of minimal pairs
item.description: We create WOGLI (Word Order in German Language Inference), the first adversarial NLI dataset for German word order that has the following properties: (i) each premise has an entailed and a non-entailed hypothesis; (ii) premise and hypotheses differ only in word order and necessary morphological changes to mark case and number.

item.title: MobileNMT: Enabling Translation in 15MB and 30ms
item.description: With the co-design of model and engine, compared with the existing system, we speed up 47. 0x and save 99. 5% of memory with only 11. 6% loss of BLEU.

item.title: ChatGPT is fun, but it is not funny! Humor is still challenging Large Language Models
item.description: In a series of exploratory experiments around jokes, i. e., generation, explanation, and detection, we seek to understand ChatGPT's capability to grasp and reproduce human humor.

item.title: A Mask Free Neural Network for Monaural Speech Enhancement
item.description: In speech enhancement, the lack of clear structural characteristics in the target speech phase requires the use of conservative and cumbersome network frameworks.

item.title: Generative Semantic Communication: Diffusion Models Beyond Bit Recovery
item.description: We prove, through an in-depth assessment of multiple scenarios, that our method outperforms existing solutions in generating high-quality images with preserved semantic information even in cases where the received content is significantly degraded.

item.title: A New Dataset and Empirical Study for Sentence Simplification in Chinese
item.description: Sentence Simplification is a valuable technique that can benefit language learners and children a lot.

item.title: Gotta: Generative Few-shot Question Answering by Prompt-based Cloze Data Augmentation
item.description: Few-shot question answering (QA) aims at precisely discovering answers to a set of questions from context passages while only a few training samples are available.

item.title: Unbalanced Optimal Transport for Unbalanced Word Alignment
item.description: Monolingual word alignment is crucial to model semantic interactions between sentences.

item.title: Zambezi Voice: A Multilingual Speech Corpus for Zambian Languages
item.description: The dataset is created for speech recognition but can be extended to multilingual speech processing research for both supervised and unsupervised learning approaches.

item.title: From the One, Judge of the Whole: Typed Entailment Graph Construction with Predicate Generation
item.description: Entailment Graphs (EGs) have been constructed based on extracted corpora as a strong and explainable form to indicate context-independent entailment relations in natural languages.

item.title: Allophant: Cross-lingual Phoneme Recognition with Articulatory Attributes
item.description: This paper proposes Allophant, a multilingual phoneme recognizer.

item.title: On the Reliability of Watermarks for Large Language Models
item.description: Large language models (LLMs) are now deployed to everyday use and positioned to produce large quantities of text in the coming decade.

item.title: PyTrial: A Comprehensive Platform for Artificial Intelligence for Drug Development
item.description: To facilitate the research and development of artificial intelligence (AI) for drug development, we developed a Python package, namely PyTrial, that implements various clinical trial tasks supported by AI algorithms.

item.title: Conditional Diffusion Models for Weakly Supervised Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: Recent advances in denoising diffusion probabilistic models have shown great success in image synthesis tasks.

item.title: One-Dimensional Deep Image Prior for Curve Fitting of S-Parameters from Electromagnetic Solvers
item.description: DIP is a technique that optimizes the weights of a randomly-initialized convolutional neural network to fit a signal from noisy or under-determined measurements.

item.title: Exploring the effects of robotic design on learning and neural control
item.description: Overall, this dissertation intimates the ability to automatically design robots that are more general purpose than current robots and that can perform various tasks while requiring less computation.
